column5: Hey guys/gals, I lost a clear Plano tackle tray full of lures on Lake Muskoka on saturday night (Feb 4). It fell out of my sled somewhere between Boyers Beach and the river. If anyone here found it, I will pay a handsome reward to get it back. Thanks
That sucks man! I hope someone finds it!  S.
I know, what a bummer. I can replace most of it but there were alot of old discontinued and customized lures that had good mojo attached to them. Icefishing sucks anyways JK

Ouch for sure.  I didn't lose my stuff, but I know the feeling. Some idiot striped all my ice gear out of the back my truck as I ate breakfast one morning.  Lots of custom baits and hard to get ones.  Ice fishing hasn't been the same since.  Good luck bud!
How was the walleye fishing at the river? I hear there are 100 people an evening out there doing good.
Not even close to a 100 guys.  Has been hit and miss out there. Slowing down now.
Not that many guys and we only got one eye. Pretty slow on Saturday. Thanks guys, I'm sure it's gone for good. If a fisherman found it, they just hit the jackpot.
